<subSubSection id="C3485ED6097EB220EC95F9F523D34DDA" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BED0D5D097EB220EC95F9F523B44C41" blockId="42.[151,1436,1577,2035]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">
<emphasis id="B926D14F097EB220EC95F9F521294C6A" bold="true" box="[151,290,1577,1603]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">Etymology:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE097EB220ED2BF9F521AA4C6A" authorityName="Hoedeman" authorityYear="1951" box="[297,417,1577,1603]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Aphaniidae" genus="Aphaniops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B926D14F097EB220ED2BF9F521AA4C6A" box="[297,417,1577,1603]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">Aphaniops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 
<emphasis id="B926D14F097EB220EDADF9F522574C6A" box="[431,604,1577,1604]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE097EB220EDADF9F522124C6A" authorityName="Nardo" authorityYear="1827" box="[431,537,1577,1603]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinodontidae" genus="Aphanius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Aphanius</taxonomicName>
-opsis
</emphasis>
, resembling 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE097EB220EEEFF9F5235C4C6A" authorityName="Nardo" authorityYear="1827" box="[749,855,1577,1603]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinodontidae" genus="Aphanius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B926D14F097EB220EEEFF9F5235C4C6A" box="[749,855,1577,1603]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">Aphanius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE097EB220EF64F9F523E44C6A" baseAuthorityName="Day" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[870,1007,1577,1603]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Aphaniidae" genus="Aphaniops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="stoliczkanus">
<emphasis id="B926D14F097EB220EF64F9F523E44C6A" box="[870,1007,1577,1603]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">stoliczkanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: named for Moravian zoologist Ferdinand Stoliczka (1838-1874) who worked in 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD097EB220EE84F99122CB4C4E" box="[646,704,1613,1639]" name="India" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">India</collectingCountry>
for a number of years.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BED0D5D097EB220ECC5F9AD23374CA2" blockId="42.[151,1436,1577,2035]" box="[199,828,1649,1675]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">
<emphasis id="B926D14F097EB220ECC5F9AD218C4CA2" bold="true" box="[199,391,1649,1675]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">Common name:</emphasis>
Arabian Killifish, Arabian Tooth-carp.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BED0D5D097EB220ECC5F949243A4CD1" blockId="42.[151,1436,1577,2035]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">
<emphasis id="B926D14F097EB220ECC5F94921454C86" bold="true" box="[199,334,1685,1711]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">Taxonomy:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE097EB220ED57F94922A84C99" authority="Day" authorityName="Day" authorityYear="1872" box="[341,675,1685,1712]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinodontidae" genus="Cyprinodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="stoliczkanus">
<emphasis id="B926D14F097EB220ED57F94922674C86" box="[341,620,1685,1711]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">Cyprinodon stoliczkanus</emphasis>
Day
</taxonomicName>
[F.] 1872:258 [Journal of the Asiatic Society of Bengal v. 41 (pt 2, nos 1-4)] from a stream at the village Joorun and along edge of the Rann River, Lodai, 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD097EB220E86BF96524AE4CFA" box="[1129,1189,1721,1747]" name="India" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">India</collectingCountry>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="EE666B9A097EB220E8B2F965251F4CFA" box="[1200,1300,1721,1747]" degrees="22" direction="north" minutes="30" orientation="latitude" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" precision="925" value="22.5">22°30’N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="EE666B9A097EB220E91DF965258A4CFA" box="[1311,1409,1721,1747]" degrees="69" direction="east" minutes="20" orientation="longitude" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" precision="925" value="69.333336">69°20’E</geoCoordinate>
. It was considered as 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE097EB220ED6AF90122FC4CDE" authority="(Day 1872)" baseAuthorityName="Day" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[360,759,1757,1783]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Aphaniidae" genus="Aphaniops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="stoliczkanus">
<emphasis id="B926D14F097EB220ED6AF901227B4CDE" box="[360,624,1757,1783]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">Aphaniops stoliczkanus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC370AC097EB220EE7DF90122E44CDE" author="Day, F." box="[639,751,1757,1783]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" pagination="258 - 260" refId="ref23046" refString="Day, F. (1872) Notes on fish, collected by Dr. Stoliczka in Kachh. Journal of the Asiatic Society of Bengal, 41 (Pt. 2, No. 1 - 4), 258 - 260." type="journal article" year="1872">Day 1872</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC370AC097EB220EF23F90124264CD1" author="Esmaeili, H. R. &amp; Teimori, A. &amp; Zarei, F. &amp; Sayyadzadeh, G." box="[801,1069,1757,1784]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" pagination="1 - 26" refId="ref23301" refString="Esmaeili, H. R., Teimori, A., Zarei, F. &amp; Sayyadzadeh, G. (2020) DNA barcoding and species delimitation of the Old World tooth-carps, family Aphaniidae Hoedeman, 1949 (Teleostei: Cyprinodontiformes). PLoS One, 15 (4), 1 - 26. https: // doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0231717" type="journal article" year="2020">
Esmaeili 
<emphasis id="B926D14F097EB220EF88F90223C84CDE" box="[906,963,1757,1783]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">et al.</emphasis>
(2020:5)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BED0D5D097EB220ECC5F8DD24F74D32" blockId="42.[151,1436,1577,2035]" box="[199,1276,1793,1820]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">
<materialsCitation id="3B3A0700097EB220ECC5F8DD24FC4D32" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3766721353" box="[199,1271,1793,1820]" collectionCode="BMNH" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="syntype">
<emphasis id="B926D14F097EB220ECC5F8DD21374D32" bold="true" box="[199,316,1793,1819]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">
<typeStatus id="54E9B3FF097EB220ECC5F8DD213C4D32" box="[199,311,1793,1819]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">Syntypes</typeStatus>
:
</emphasis>
(28) AMS B.7730-31 (2), 
<collectionCode id="ED439598097EB220EE65F8DE22B04D35" box="[615,699,1794,1820]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">BMNH</collectionCode>
1889.2.1.2065-2074 (orig. 21), ZSI 1477-78 (1, 1)
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BED0D5D097EB220ECC5F8F9229D4D85" blockId="42.[151,1436,1577,2035]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">
<emphasis id="B926D14F097EB220ECC5F8F921AB4D16" bold="true" box="[199,416,1829,1855]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">Short description:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE097EB220EDA4F8F922A64D16" baseAuthorityName="Day" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[422,685,1829,1855]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Aphaniidae" genus="Aphaniops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="stoliczkanus">
<emphasis id="B926D14F097EB220EDA4F8F922A64D16" box="[422,685,1829,1855]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">Aphaniops stoliczkanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from the other 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE097EB220E80FF8F9248E4D16" authorityName="Hoedeman" authorityYear="1951" box="[1037,1157,1829,1855]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Aphaniidae" genus="Aphaniops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B926D14F097EB220E80FF8F9248E4D16" box="[1037,1157,1829,1855]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">Aphaniops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Arabian Peninsula by combination of the following characters: male usually with wide grey or brown bars at caudal peduncle; tip of dorsal fin reaching to end of hypural complex in nuptial males larger than 
<quantity id="4CAAA0B8097EB220EFCAF8B1241D4DA1" box="[968,1046,1901,1928]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" unit="mm" value="40.0">40 mm</quantity>
SL; female with a midlateral series of narrow bars, not much wider in upper part.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BED0D5D097EB220ECC5F86923D34DDA" blockId="42.[151,1436,1577,2035]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">
<emphasis id="B926D14F097EB220ECC5F86921CD4DE6" bold="true" box="[199,454,1973,1999]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">General distribution:</emphasis>
Middle East: Shores of Red Sea and Gulf of 
<collectingRegion id="4996C3BF097EB220EFC0F869240A4DE6" box="[962,1025,1973,1999]" country="Yemen" name="'Adan" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">Aden</collectingRegion>
, and easternmost Mediterranean Sea basin; 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD097EB220ECE3F805213C4DDA" box="[225,311,2009,2035]" name="Yemen" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">Socotra</collectingCountry>
(northwestern Indian Ocean). Habitat: freshwater, brackish.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF2D5DD5097FB221EC95FA8D24B74F40" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6541669" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6541669" box="[151,1212,1361,1386]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6541669/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="494" startId="43.[151,250,1361,1385]" targetBox="[151,1436,181,1337]" targetPageId="43">
